bib_record.title: -THE TOTAL NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS OF CR-50, CR-52, NI-62 AND NI-64 IN THE ENERGY REGION 10-300 KEV.-

free_txt: 3 MV PULSED VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR
.EXPERIMENTAL CROSS SECTIONS WERE CALCULATED FROM
TRANSMISSION T AS   SIGMA = -LOG(T)/N  WHERE N IS
TOTAL NO. OF SAMPLE ATOMS PER BARN. THUS THEY ARE
RESOLUTION-BROADENED AND GIVEN PER SAMPLE ATOM (INCL.
O ATOMS IN CR-OXIDE SAMPLES AND ISOTOPIC IMPURITIES).
MULTI-LEVEL R-MATRIX PARAMETERS DETERMINED
BY LEAST-SQUARES FIT SIMULTANEOUSLY TO THIN- AND
THICK-SAMPLE TRANSMISSION DATA (CODE FANAL2,FROEHNER).
.UNBROADENED CROSS SECTIONS OF PURE ISOTOPES WERE THEN
CALCULATED FROM RESONANCE PARAMETERS.
.TRANSMISSIONS ARE CORRECTED FOR BACKGROUND AND DEAD
TIME (AND CR-OXIDE DATA FOR 0.38 PC. H2O CONTAMINANT).
.TRANSMISSION DATA, FITS AND CALCULATED PURE-ISOTOPE
CROSS SECTIONS ARE PLOTTED IN KFK-1517, FIGS. 1-8.
.SOMEWHAT MORE COMPLETE RESONANCE PARAMETER TABLES
(INCLUDING MEASURED RADIATION WIDTHS) ARE GIVEN IN
KFK-2046, -NEUTRON CAPTURE IN THE KEV ENERGY RANGE
IN STRUCTURAL MATERIALS FOR FAST REACTORS,-
PROC. OF A NEACRP-NEANDC SPECIALIST MEETING,
KARLSRUHE, MAY 1973 (EXFOR ACCESSION NUMBER
LI-6 LOADED GLASS SCINTILLATOR NE 905 AND
XP 1040 PHOTOMULTIPLIER.
.ERRORS OF EXP. CROSS SECTIONS ARE STATISTICAL.
RESONANCE ENERGIES ARE DUE TO TIMEING ERRORS
.                    WIDTHS ARE DUE TO COUNTING
STATISTICS PROPAGATED THROUGH LEAST-SQUARES FIT.
.ERRORS OF CALCULATED CROSS SECTIONS ARE DUE TO WIDTH
UNCERTAINTIES, INDICATIVE ONLY (ENERGY UNCERTAINTY
AND CORRELATIONS NEGLECTED).
3 MV PULSED VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR
PROTON-LITHIUM 7, THICK LI-TARGET.
TIME OF FLIGHT, TRANSMISSION MEASUREMENT.
FLIGHT PATH 4.962 M, PULSE WIDTH 1 NS, REPETITION RATE
250 KHZ, CHANNEL WIDTH 2 NS. 4 RUNS PER ISOTOPE (THIN
AND THICK SAMPLE, LOW AND HIGH ENERGIES), EXCEPT FOR
NI-64 WHERE ONLY 1 SAMPLE WAS USED AT LOW ENERGIES.
.ABSOLUTE, TRANSMISSION MEASUREMENT.
NEUTRONS.
CROSS SECTIONS ARE CALCULATED FROM PARAMETERS AND
CROSS SECTION ERRORS ARE CALCULATED WITHOUT ACCOUNT OF
ENERGY SCALE UNCERTAINTY (0.3 PERCENT) AND ERROR
COVARIANCES.
.POTENTIAL SCATTERING PARAMETERS OF KFK-1517 WERE
REPLACED BY NEW SET VALID FOR ENTIRE ENERGY RANGE,
A = 4.2+-0.1 FM  (R-MATRIX CHANNEL RADIUS),
S = (3+-1)/10**4 (DISTANT-LEVEL STRENGTH FUNCTION).
ALL RADIATION WIDTHS WERE ASSUMED AS GG = 2.0+-0.5 EV.
.PRIVATE COMMUNICATION FROM FROEHNER 05/72.
